  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nDuring testing of Embedded ChainSpecs I've noticed, that when providing invalid chainspec (empty, json invalid etc) Runner or Launcher will throw proper exception but user is unable just to close app using CTRL + C. Need to close entire cmd and type command again.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n1. Go to chainspec location\r\n2. Create new json file with just empty json chars {}\r\n3. Open cmd on nethermind directory\r\n4. Start Nethermind.Runner.exe with flag --Init.ChainSpecPath \"path/to/new/json/spec\"\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nAfter exception thrown about empty chainspec, when user hits CTRL+C app should stop and user should be able to reuse a command after json fixes\r\n\r\n**Desktop (please complete the following information):**\r\n - Windows 11, Nethermind from master branch\r\n",
